playing over stereo]

20:46.916 --> 20:50.500
-Can we change this music?
-Come on. Driver's choice.

21:03.000 --> 21:05.458
-Pete's sake.
-All right, just pull over.

21:06.125 --> 21:07.000
Yep, I know.

21:33.708 --> 21:35.916
-How you doing, officer?
-Good morning.

21:36.000 --> 21:38.125
Shh. Let him handle it.

21:38.958 --> 21:41.916
Uh, why'd you stop me, officer?

21:42.000 --> 21:45.166
-I'll ask the questions. Where you headed?
-Lancaster.

21:48.375 --> 21:49.708
You folks all right?

21:50.541 --> 21:54.500
We're okay. He's new to driving.
He has a permit.

21:55.333 --> 21:56.291
Can I see it?

21:56.750 --> 21:58.958
Whoa! Keep your hands
where I can see them.

22:01.708 --> 22:04.416
Whoa. He's trying to show you his permit.

22:06.708 --> 22:07.625
Nice and easy.

22:24.958 --> 22:26.916
What was the reason for the stop, officer?

22:27.000 --> 22:28.666
-Who are you?
-His father.

22:32.000 --> 22:32.916
He's adopted.

22:33.750 --> 22:35.833
Well, he was going a little fast.

22:38.208 --> 22:39.416
Slow down, kid.

22:55.333 --> 22:57.333
-You dodged a bullet.

22:58.041 --> 22:58.875
Yeah.

23:00.333 --> 23:02.375
You just beat your first ticket.

23:14.541 --> 23:18.750
Rise and shine! It's the big game today.
The biggest!

23:18.833 --> 23:21.833
Come on, Colin! Get up!

23:22.708 --> 23:24.208
Resistance is futile!

23:25.791 --> 23:26.625
Yeah.

23:32.125 --> 23:32.958
You're right.

23:33.833 --> 23:35.416
Resistance is futile.

23:36.125 --> 23:39.208
-What's that? What'd you say?
-What you just said.

23:40.083 --> 23:42.291
Resistance is futile.
I'm agreeing with you.

23:42.375 --> 23:45.250
No. I said, I'm gonna make a strudel.

23:46.333 --> 23:47.166
So weird.

23:55.625 --> 23:56.541
How's your arm?

23:58.416 --> 23:59.541
I'm ready, Dad.

24:00.125 --> 24:02.250
You look ready. You look like a pro.

24:04.000 --> 24:07.000
See what a clean shave can do? Let's go.

24:18.000 --> 24:20.041
-You doing okay back there?
-Huh?

24:20.125 --> 24:21.666
You doing okay back there?

24:22.458 --> 24:23.708
Yeah, I'm doing okay.

24:32.250 --> 24:35.625
Yo. Why are you dressed
like you fix computers?

24:38.208 --> 24:39.041
Whatever.

24:45.791 --> 24:46.625
What's up, bro?

24:48.166 --> 24:49.875
They play in the tournament?

24:51.583 --> 24:52.541
Watch your gear.

24:55.583 --> 25:00.208
Who steals more than his son? Kid
stole a water bottle with my name on it.

25:00.875 --> 25:02.708
Seriously, don't sweat it, bro.

25:11.708 --> 25:15.250
-You mind having your boys keep it down?
-Yeah, we got you.

25:24.916 --> 25:26.208
I hate this, man.

25:30.833 --> 25:35.875
-Where did you get that shirt from?
-A spot in Vallejo. Where you from?

25:38.208 --> 25:39.250
Turlock.

25:39.833 --> 25:41.291
I think I heard of that,

25:41.791 --> 25:44.375
with all the Confederate flags
and country music and shit.

25:45.458 --> 25:48.250
-That's about right.
-Hey, I'm Dwayne, man.

25:48.333 --> 25:50.000
Didn't know
what he was talking about.

25:50.083 --> 25:51.583
-I'm Colin.
-Stupid.

25:51.666 --> 25:53.708
-Shut up, man.
-Yo, hey, y'all settle down.

25:53.791 --> 25:56.500
-I'm not trying to get kicked out again.
-Again?

25:57.583 --> 25:59.541
They threw us out of here
year before last.

25:59.625 --> 26:01.625
They wouldn't let us stay here last year.

26:02.666 --> 26:03.666
What? Why?

26:05.666 --> 26:11.083
Hey, Keith, Jontavious. Homey wanna know
what we did to get kicked out last time.

26:12.041 --> 26:15.000
-Why you think? For being Black.
-Right?

26:15.083 --> 26:17.625
Yeah. Saying we were loitering
and making guests uncomfortable.

26:17.708 --> 26:21.541
White people were making me
uncomfortable. You know what I mean?

26:22.166 --> 26:24.083
-On my moms, we didn't do nothing.
-No.

26:24.833 --> 26:26.833
I'm sorry. That's messed up.

26:27.416 --> 26:30.208
It is what it is.
Coach says you gotta pick your battles.

26:30.291 --> 26:33.333
So we stay here, get our win and bounce.

26:35.833 --> 26:37.625
Bet they don't bother your team, huh?

26:40.250 --> 26:41.125
Not all of us.

26:42.791 --> 26:43.750
Man.

26:43.833 --> 26:44.708
Come on.

26:49.041 --> 26:52.000
-I should get going.
-All right, player. Peace.

26:52.083 --> 26:52.916
Peace.

26:55.916 --> 27:00.750
Homeboy tuck his shirt in so tight.
Is that how they get down in Turlock?

27:01.833 --> 27:04.666
Man, I ain't mad at him.
He just trying to live.

27:05.875 --> 27:07.500
All right. Let's check in.

27:08.875 --> 27:09.708
Okay.

27:14.125 --> 27:15.125
Thank you.

27:18.208 --> 27:19.041
Sorry.

27:22.333 --> 27:23.208
You two good?

27:24.000 --> 27:25.208
-Okay.
-Fine. Thanks.

27:26.875 --> 27:29.291
Yeah, I'm good too. Thanks.

27:32.666 --> 27:36.625
-Somebody's feisty today.
-Yeah, I don't know what his problem was.

27:37.583 --> 27:38.916
I'm talking about you.

27:42.083 --> 27:45.916
And after all that,
in the last game of the tournament,

27:46.000 --> 27:48.666
I had to face the same dumb umpire

27:48.750 --> 27:52.166
and some dude who was stalling,
trying to psych me out.

27:55.875 --> 27:57.041
Look at this guy.

27:57.125 --> 27:58.083
What an ass.

28:04.875 --> 28:06.125
Time-out.

28:09.375 --> 28:10.958
This guy's a showboat.

28:14.833 --> 28:15.666
Play ball.

28:18.750 --> 28:20.458
Look alive, guys, look alive!

28:24.958 --> 28:25.958
Ball!

28:26.041 --> 28:28.416
-He's crowding the plate.
-You got this, Colin.

28:29.333 --> 28:31.750
-Come on, Kaepernick.
-Let's go, you got it!

28:31.833 --> 28:35.083
What was that? Get some glasses!

28:38.375 --> 28:39.666
Let's go, drive it.

28:44.583 --> 28:47.166
-Ball!
-Hey, he's crowding the plate!

28:50.208 --> 28:51.583
Nice pitch, nice pitch.

28:52.375 --> 28:54.541
Settle down, Colin, you got it.

28:55.958 --> 28:57.750
Who says resistance is futile?

29:05.958 --> 29:07.208
Watch it, Kaepernick!

29:07.291 --> 29:10.375
One more and you'll have the showers
to yourself. Get my meaning?

29:10.458 --> 29:13.208
-Don't test me.
-It's okay, Colin!

29:16.166 --> 29:18.791
I know what you're thinking.
I wasn't really gonna hit him.

29:18.875 --> 29:20.833
Let's go, Kap! Down the barrel!

29:20.916 --> 29:23.166
I needed him to back off the plate,

29:23.250 --> 29:24.791
so I could strike his ass out.

29:26.125 --> 29:28.416
I guess what I learned that summer was

29:28.500 --> 29:31.250
they're not always
gonna give you a fair call.

29:33.041 --> 29:36.208
But you can't let them stop you
from playing the game.

29:36.291 --> 29:38.166
-Strike!
-Attaboy!

29:58.916 --> 30:00.125
Can I talk to you?

30:08.375 --> 30:11.333
Heard you won the championship.
Congratulations.

30:13.208 --> 30:14.041
Thanks.

30:16.666 --> 30:18.375
Well, have fun.

30:18.958 --> 30:21.750
Be careful. Hope to see you
back here next year.

30:23.000 --> 30:24.875
Glad to see you're one of the good ones.

30:28.375 --> 30:29.458
Hey!

30:31.458 --> 30:33.958
-What do you mean by that?
-By what?

30:34.708 --> 30:36.750
One of the good ones. What does that mean?

30:37.833 --> 30:42.500
It means you're nice.
Not like those other boys in the lobby.

30:44.083 --> 30:48.083
You remind me of that one that-- The nerd
with glasses. I meant it as a compliment.

30:49.750 --> 30:51.125
It's not a compliment.

30:51.208 --> 30:53.958
You don't have to get angry.
I was trying to be nice.

30:57.791 --> 30:59.583
Maybe you aren't one of the good ones.

31:04.916 --> 31:07.875
Oh, he must not know
any Black people in real life.

31:08.750 --> 31:09.750
Over the years,

31:10.250 --> 31:13.916
there have been some very popular
TV shows starring Black people.

31:14.000 --> 31:17.208
These shows share archetypal
Black characters,

31:17.291 --> 31:20.458
including social outcasts
who assimilate or conform.

31:21.125 --> 31:24.250
Like Carlton Banks, or Steve Urkel.

31:24.333 --> 31:27.625
Wow. You guys have got
some real A-list people here.

31:27.708 --> 31:29.833
White people love these dudes.

31:30.333 --> 31:33.083
From the way they dress,
the way they talk...

31:33.166 --> 31:34.208
You're our man.

31:34.875 --> 31:38.291
...even the way they dance.
It's all so non-threatening.

31:38.375 --> 31:39.500
James Spurlock.

31:39.583 --> 31:42.833
We call him Toofer, for two-for-one.
He's a Black guy and a Harvard guy.

31:42.916 --> 31:44.666
These characters
have come to be known

31:44.750 --> 31:46.375
by the term "Acceptable Negro."

31:46.458 --> 31:51.250
The Acceptable Negro is a Black character
who inhabits white characteristics...

31:52.833 --> 31:55.333
who makes white people feel comfortable.

31:56.625 --> 32:00.291
The Acceptable Negro
is a white man's creation.

32:01.541 --> 32:06.125
Thing is, white people don't get
to decide who's acceptable to us.

32:06.833 --> 32:12.875
We can rock with Steve Urkel
and Steve Biko and Marcus Garvey.

32:14.416 --> 32:15.333
Huey Newton.

32:16.333 --> 32:17.666
Ida B. Wells.

32:18.791 --> 32:19.833
Toni Morrison.

32:20.666 --> 32:21.750
Fannie Lou Hamer.

32:24.125 --> 32:25.125
Assata Shakur.

32:26.250 --> 32:27.541
Patrice Lumumba.

32:28.750 --> 32:30.000
Kwame Nkrumah.

32:31.916 --> 32:33.041
James Baldwin.

32:35.125 --> 32:37.875
You know, some of the good ones.

32:38.750 --> 32:40.750
As Langston Hughes once said:

32:41.541 --> 32:42.458
"Negroes

32:43.000 --> 32:46.583
Sweet and docile
Meek, humble, and kind

32:47.250 --> 32:50.416
Beware the day
They change their mind"
